            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Vitellio Messala Vi<expan><ex>p</ex><abbr>stano</abbr></expan> Gallo co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulibus</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">X Id</supplied>us Septembres <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Faenius Eumenes scri<supplied reason="lost">pserat</supplied> <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost">se</supplied> con<expan><ex>s</ex><abbr>ciente</abbr></expan> secum <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aio</ex></expan> Sulpicio Fausto <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">ad vadimonium non</supplied> venire caussa quae<supplied reason="lost">sita</supplied> <lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">et dato de</supplied> ea re ultro citro cognitore respondit <lb n="6"/><supplied reason="lost">se remitte</supplied>re vadimonium quod Sulpici <lb n="7"/>Fausti cognitorem eo nomine haberet <lb n="8"/><supplied reason="lost">deinde</supplied> <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> Sulpicius Faustus eo nomine <lb n="9"/><supplied reason="lost">stipulatus est</supplied> spopondit acceptam pecuniam <lb n="10"/><supplied reason="lost">se habere</supplied> Filenius <note>sic</note> Eumenes serv<expan><ex>u</ex><abbr>s</abbr></expan> <lb n="11"/><supplied reason="lost">adfuerunt</supplied> heredes cum familiaribus
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Tabula Pompeiana. Der Text bezieht sich auf das vadimonium aus Tabula Pompeiana 41. (B): AE 1978, Sbordone: teilweise völlig falsche Lesung und Ergänzung; AE 1984: ebenfalls Leseabweichungen. (C): ungenaues Tagesdatum. Lesung Sbordone nach G. Camodeca (Mitteilung EDR v. 05.07.2007) völlig verkehrt; verbesserte Lesung in EDR.</p>
            </div>
